STACY KEACH: This is the scene of the crime. The child was locked in a room and tied to a potty chair for most of her life. Completely restrained, she was forced to sit alone day after day and often through the night. She\hich\af0\dbch\af14\loch\f0 
 had little to look at and no one to talk to for more than ten years.
\par }{\insrsid11485374\charrsid2827064 \hich\af0\dbch\af14\loch\f0 1 Where did Genie spend her time?
\par }{\insrsid8799195\charrsid2827064 \hich\af0\dbch\af14\loch\f0 ...}{\insrsid8853670\charrsid2827064 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af14\loch\f0 SUSAN CURTISS: The indications are that she was beaten for making noise and consequently, had learned, basically, not to vocalize. And she really di\hich\af0\dbch\af14\loch\f0 
dn't vocalize very much at all. When I first met her, she was silent most of the time.
\par }{\insrsid11485374\charrsid2827064 \hich\af0\dbch\af14\loch\f0 2 What would happen if Genie would make any noise?
\par }{\insrsid8799195\charrsid2827064 \hich\af0\dbch\af14\loch\f0 ...}{\insrsid8853670\charrsid2827064 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af14\loch\f0 For four nights running, they wired Genie to instruments that measured the electrical activity in her brain while \hich\af0\dbch\af14\loch\f0 
she slept. What they found was an unusually high number of so-called sleep spindles, the dense bunching patterns that look like spindles on a spinning machine. This was an abnormal brain wave pattern. The sleep studies raised a question that would puzzle 
\hich\af0\dbch\af14\loch\f0 t\hich\af0\dbch\af14\loch\f0 he Genie team for years. Was Genie brain damaged from her years of abuse, or had she been retarded from birth?\hich\af0\dbch\af14\loch\f0  
