\par }{\insrsid8853670\charrsid2827064 \hich\af0\dbch\af14\loch\f0 Chomsky declared that we acquire language not just because we are taught it, but because we are born with the principles of language. They're in our genes. We have language, Chomsk
\hich\af0\dbch\af14\loch\f0 
y said, because of nature, not just nurture. Then, along came a neuropsychologist to add his own twist to the theory. Eric Lenneberg agreed we're born with the principles of language, but acclaimed there is a deadline for applying them. If a first languag
\hich\af0\dbch\af14\loch\f0 e\hich\af0\dbch\af14\loch\f0  isn't acquired by puberty, he said, it may be too late.\hich\af0\dbch\af14\loch\f0  }{\insrsid8799195\charrsid2827064 
