one" to Victor, and he shows some ingenuity. He goes off, he gets a hammer, and he smashes the stone. "Cut a cup." He picks up the cup and hurls it on the floor, and it shatters. "Eat a broom." This time, he changes the noun, goes off and gets a piece of 
\hich\af0\dbch\af14\loch\f0 b\hich\af0\dbch\af14\loch\f0 read and devours it. This was Itard, constantly analyzing, upping the ante, pushing the kid toward civilization, toward the skills that we have.}{\insrsid8799195\charrsid2827064 
